doc.ContractDescription: EARLY THEORETICAL MODELS OF SATURN'S UPPER ATMOSPHERE PREDICTED AN IONOSPHERE DOMINATED BY H+ WITH A PEAK ELECTRON DENSITY (NMAX) OF ~10^5 E- CM-3 THAT VARIED LITTLE THROUGHOUT THE DAY. INSTEAD, SPACECRAFT OBSERVATIONS HAVE REVEALED AN IONOSPHERE WITH A 1-2 ORDER OF MAGNITUDE DIURNAL VARIATION IN NMAX, WITH VALUES OF ~10^4 E- CM-3 NEAR SATURN DAWN AND DUSK. SUBSEQUENT THEORETICAL MODELS INTRODUCED ADDITIONAL PHOTOCHEMICAL LOSS PROCESSES THAT CONVERTED THE LONG-LIVED ATOMIC ION H+ INTO SHORT-LIVED MOLECULAR IONS, THEREBY REDUCING THE NET ELECTRON DENSITY AND DRIVING A STRONGER DIURNAL VARIATION IN NMAX, YET NONE HAVE SO FAR SUCCEEDED IN REPRODUCING THE OBSERVED VARIATIONS. THIS MODEL-DATA DISCREPANCY IMPLIES EITHER A FUNDAMENTAL MISUNDERSTANDING IN THE THEORY OF SATURN'S IONOSPHERE, OR A MISAPPLICATION OF QUANTITIES OBSERVED BY SPACECRAFT IN SATURN'S MAGNETOSPHERE TO THE PARAMETERS WITHIN ITS IONOSPHERE. WE PROPOSE HERE TO EXAMINE BOTH POSSIBILITIES IN DETAIL. WE WILL MAKE USE OF THREE MAIN INGREDIENTS IN THIS STUDY: (1) THE SATURN THERMOSPHERE-IONOSPHERE MODEL (STIM), A ROBUST SUITE OF 1-D, 2-D, AND 3-D MODELS OF SATURN'S UPPER ATMOSPHERE DEVELOPED BY THE MEMBERS OF THIS PROPOSAL, (2) RADIO OCCULTATION MEASUREMENTS FROM CASSINI'S RADIO SCIENCE SUBSYSTEM (RSS) INSTRUMENT, AND (3) SATURN ELECTROSTATIC DISCHARGE (SED) MEASUREMENTS FROM CASSINI'S RADIO AND PLASMA WAVE SCIENCE (RPWS) INSTRUMENT. THESE WILL BE COMBINED TO ADDRESS TWO MAIN RELATED SCIENCE TOPICS: (1) WHAT PHYSICAL PROCESSES IN STIM ARE REQUIRED TO GENERATE OBSERVED DIURNAL VARIATIONS IN NMAX, AND ARE THE RESULTING MODEL PARAMETERS CONSISTENT WITH OTHER OBSERVATIONS? (2) HOW ACCURATE IS THE SED-DERIVED REPRESENTATION OF DIURNAL VARIATIONS IN SATURN'S IONOSPHERE? HOW DOES ATTENUATION OF RADIO WAVES IN THE LOWER IONOSPHERE AFFECT SED ANALYSIS? CAN IT ALSO EXPLAIN THE LACK OF EQUIVALENT RADIO EMISSION AT JUPITER? IT IS IMPORTANT TO RESOLVE THE ABOVE MODEL-DATA DISCREPANCY. A MISUNDERSTANDING OF SATURN IONOSPHERIC SCIENCE HAS DIRECT IMPACT ON A NUMBER OF RELATED ISSUES, SUCH AS IONOSPHERIC CONDUCTANCES AND THEREFORE MAGNETOSPHERE-ATMOSPHERE COUPLING AND MAGNETOSPHERIC DYNAMICS. THE WORK IN THIS PROPOSAL WILL ENHANCE THE SCIENTIFIC RETURN FROM CASSINI, AND IS ALSO DIRECTLY RELEVANT TO THE OTHER GIANT PLANETS, AS THEY HAVE VERY SIMILAR UPPER ATMOSPHERIC CHEMISTRY.
